FT  04 DEC 93 / World Stock Markets: Mexico
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mexican share prices soared to close at an all-time high, propelled by local
and foreign buying of market heavyweight Telmex. The 36-share IPC index
gained 53.31, a rise of 2.35 percent, to 2,324.09.
Trading in Telmex accounted for 53m of the total. Telmex ADRs rose  7/8 to
58 1/4 , while in the local market the L shares gained 2.04 per cent and the
As 1.81 percent.
